    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-8">Last updated: April 2026 | Based on public information, published methodologies, and client outcomes</p>

    <img src="/images/content/stat-77-percent.svg" alt="UK AI visibility research data" class="w-full rounded-xl mb-8 mt-6" loading="lazy">
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">ChatGPT is where most people first encounter AI search. When someone asks ChatGPT to recommend a business, the answer draws on a combination of training data, Bing search results, and real-time web browsing. Getting your business into those answers requires a specific approach.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The Bing relationship matters. ChatGPT uses Bing as its primary search backend for real-time queries. That means Bing indexing, Bing Places listings, and structured data that Bing can read all influence whether ChatGPT recommends your business. Most traditional SEO agencies optimise exclusively for Google and miss this entirely.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-10">Assessed on: understanding of the ChatGPT-Bing relationship, multi-platform testing (not just Google), practical methodology for ChatGPT visibility, and published results or case studies.</p>

